        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare congenital disorder of glycosylation characterized by cerebral and portal vein thrombosis portal hypertension macrocephaly and persistent absence seizures. Additional reported features include mild to moderate global developmental delay and intellectual disability as well as thrombocytopenia. Brain imaging may show variable stages of infarction and cerebral and cerebellar atrophy."
        },
